I'm a little confused how to check the tensors are initialised.

I just did the following, after the .fit()

for t in tf.get_default_graph().as_graph_def().node:
    print(t.name)

Along with changing one line to:
input_tensor=model.input,classes_tensor=labels_tensor, scores_tensor=model.output)

Which seems to show 'convolution2d_1_W' is part of the graph.

When attempting to load I get:

tensorflow.python.framework.errors_impl.FailedPreconditionError: Attempting to use uninitialized value convolution2d_1_W

Cheers

body:
I'm a little confused how to check the tensors are initialised.

I just did the following, after the .fit() 

```
for t in tf.get_default_graph().as_graph_def().node:
    print(t.name)
```
Along with changing one line to:
input_tensor=model.input,classes_tensor=labels_tensor, scores_tensor=model.output)

Which seems to show 'convolution2d_1_W' is part of the graph.

When attempting to load I get:
```
tensorflow.python.framework.errors_impl.FailedPreconditionError: Attempting to use uninitialized value convolution2d_1_W
```

Cheers
